{{notability|Products|date=December 2012}}
'''Astro Base''' was a [[toy]] made by the [[Ideal Toy Company|Ideal]] company in the early 1960s. The toy ran on 4 [[D battery|D Cell batteries]]. Besides a power switch, it had several features that includes the following modes of operation:
==Modes of operation== * ''Astro Scope'': Switch to Astro Scope and a scene of [[spaceships]], [[rockets]], and [[jet aircraft|jets]] rotates through a [[viewfinder]] just below a [[radar dome]] on the top of the toy. A button on the [[System console|console]] let the user "fire" at objects seen on the screen, which would pause the rotating images and emit a [[machine-gun]] style sound. * ''Space Lock'': A [[crane (machine)|crane]] emerges from the [[Trapdoor|hatch]] on one side of the toy. This crane has a [[hoist (device)|hoist]] operation that can be used to raise or lower a plastic [[astronaut]] figure, or other objects that the user may have that can be connected to the hook at the end of a chain. The main purpose of this crane is to insert or remove the astronaut from a [[scout car]]. * ''Scout Car'': The scout car can be plugged into a [[port]] on the console and controlled by a two position [[switch]] marked "turn" and "drive" that can actually be used to steer the vehicle with a bit of practice. The scout car also has [[missiles]] that can be launched.
Ideal made two variations of the Astro Base. The original "all red" version featured a lighted Astro Scope that illuminated the pictures spinning around the Astro Scope. Ideal Toys discontinued this version and offered the common "red and white" version.
