{{Infobox song contest country |Name = Netherlands |Flag = Flag of the Netherlands.svg |Member station = [[TROS]] |National selection event = Eurovision Dans Festival |ESC apps = 2 |ESC first = [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2007|2007]] |ESC best = 12th, [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2007|2007]] |ESC worst = Last, [[Eurovision Dance Contest 2008|2008]] |Website = |EBU page = http://www.eurovisiondance.tv/nl.php }}
The [[Netherlands]] took part in the first [[Eurovision Dance Contest]] in 2007. The couple representing the country was chosen on 4 August 2007. [[Alexandra Matteman]] & [[Redmond Valk]] won the televoting and the jury's votes and performed the [[cha-cha-cha (dance)|Cha-Cha-Cha]] and [[Rhumba|Rumba]] in [[London]]. The Netherlands came twelfth after receiving 34 points from 7 countries. The Netherlands is one of only two countries never to finish in the top 10, the other being [[Sweden]].
Due to poor results, the Netherlands withdrew from the planned Eurovision Dance Contest 2009 in Baku. The [[Third Eurovision Dance Contest]] has been cancelled indefinitely.<ref>{{cite web|last1=Granger|first1=Anthony|title=What caused the death of the Eurovision Dance Contest?|url=http://eurovoix.com/2011/05/29/what-caused-the-death-of-the-eurovision-dance-contest-p1/|website=Eurovoix.xom|publisher=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=22 June 2014|date=29 May 2011}}</ref>
