{{Infobox company | name = Out of the Park Developments GmbH & Co.KG | logo = | type = | industry = [[Video games]] | fate = | predecessor = <!-- or: | predecessors = --> | successor = <!-- or: | successors = --> | founded = {{Start date and age|1999}} | founders = Markus Heinsohn, Andreas Raht | defunct = <!-- {{End date|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | hq_location_city = [[Hollern-Twielenfleth]] | hq_location_country = Germany | area_served = <!-- or: | areas_served = --> | key_people = | products = ''[[Out of the Park Baseball]]'', ''[[Franchise Hockey Manager]]'' | owner = <!-- or: | owners = --> | num_employees = | num_employees_year = <!-- Year of num_employees data (if known) --> | parent = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
'''Out of the Park Developments GmbH & Co.KG''' is a German [[video game developer]] based in [[Hollern-Twielenfleth]]. Founded by Markus Heinsohn and Andreas Raht in 1999, the studio specialises in [[text sim]]-style [[sports game]]s, and as produced notable franchises, such as ''[[Out of the Park Baseball]]'' and ''[[Franchise Hockey Manager]]''.
== History ==
Out of the Park Developments was founded in 1999, by current [[managing director]]s Markus Heinsohn and Andreas Raht.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.gamesindustry.biz/articles/out-of-the-park-baseball-8-metacritic-s-2007-pc-game-of-the-year-being-given-away-for-free |title=Out of the Park Baseball 8 |date=10 September 2009 |website=[[GamesIndustry.biz]] |publisher=[[Gamer Network]] |accessdate=15 September 2017}}</ref>
On 21 December 2016, Out of the Park Developments announced that they had received [[Metacritic]]'s 2016 PC Game of the Year Award for ''[[Out of the Park Baseball 17]]''.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.gamasutra.com/view/pressreleases/288305/Out_of_the_Park_Baseball_17_Named_Metacriticrsquos_2016_PCGame_of_The_Year_and_for_the_first_time_ever_surpasses_100000units_sold.php |title=Out of the Park Baseball 17 Named Metacritic's 2016 PC Game of The Year and, for the first time ever, surpasses 100,000 units sold |date=22 December 2016 |website=[[Gamasutra]] |publisher=[[UBM TechWeb]] |accessdate=15 September 2017}}</ref>
